# Generated by tools/render-etv-next.py from the station config — never authored
# by hand, so ignore by pattern (channel count can change). The committed
# normalization.default.json and presentation.example.json do NOT match these.
examples/etv-next/lineup.json
examples/etv-next/channel*.json
examples/etv-next/presentation.json
examples/output/
tools/__pycache__/
# examples/channels/ holds the channels the dev station actually RUNS, and
# examples/station.yaml globs it. Personal channels live here and are ignored;
# only the runnable committed one is tracked. Ignore-then-negate rather than
# naming personal files, so renaming or adding one can't silently leak it into
# the repo (an exact-name ignore breaks the moment the file moves).
#
# Worked sample channels live in examples/samples/ instead — they are test
# fixtures, not station channels. Most are query channels that need a populated
# catalog, so registering them with the dev station would fail it at startup.
# They are tracked wholesale; nothing personal belongs there.
examples/channels/*
!examples/channels/lavfi-test.yaml
examples/blocks/
examples/overlays/marquee_overlay.toml
examples/overlays/showcase_overlay.toml
examples/overlays/scripts/
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
